##Question 4 - Convert 0 runtime into NAs in new variable movies_runtime and then count NAs again

movies_selected <- movies_selected %>% 
  mutate(movies_runtime = na_if(runtime, "0"),
         .after = runtime)
  summary(is.na(movies_selected))
   title          runtime        movies_runtime    budget

##Question 5 - Impute missing values in runtime with median runtime and check for missing values

movies_imputed <- movies_selected %>% 
  mutate(runtime = coalesce(movies_runtime, 
                            median(movies_runtime, na.rm = TRUE)))
movies_imputed
summary(is.na(movies_imputed))

##Question 6 - Find movies with 10 shortest and 10 longest runtimes using slice_min and slice_max

movies_imputed %>% 
  slice_min(runtime, n = 10)

movies_imputed %>% 
  slice_max(runtime, n= 10)

##Question 7 - Use the if_else function to replace budgets below $100 with the median budget

movies_imputed <- movies_imputed %>% 
  mutate(budget = if_else(budget < 100, median(budget, na.rm = TRUE), budget))

##Extention 1 - Use case_when to create a new budget type column

movies_imputed <- movies_imputed %>% 
  mutate(
    movie_budgets = case_when(
      budget < 12000000 ~ "Small Budget",
      between(budget, 12000000, 40000000) ~ "Medium Budget",
      budget > 40000000 ~ "Big Budget"
    )
  )
movies_imputed %>% 
  count(movie_budgets)
